parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heater core can cause hot coolant to escape into the passenger compartment, potentially injuring the driver and impairing their vision, leading to a vehicle accident.
symptoms: Hot coolant pouring or spraying into the passenger compartment
steam clouding on window surfaces
impaired driver vision.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rusting of the engine block can cause damage to the water jacket and oil feed line, leading to costly repairs or even complete engine failure.
symptoms: Rusting of the engine block
damage to the water jacket and oil feed line.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A vehicle fire can cause significant damage to the vehicle and potentially harm the occupants.
symptoms: Vehicle catching on fire
sudden and unexpected ignition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heater core can cause hot steam and water to leak into the passenger compartment, leading to fogged windows, reduced visibility, and increased risk of accidents. Additionally, the sudden release of hot fluids can cause burns or injuries to occupants.
symptoms: Hot steam and water coming through vents and from under the dash
fogged windows
coolant leak on the inside and outside of the vehicle
strange noise coming from the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Accelerator Pedal Sticking/Fuel Throttle Cable Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sticking of the accelerator pedal or failure of the fuel throttle cable can cause the vehicle to experience sudden acceleration, making it difficult to control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The gas pedal falls to the floor
the vehicle experiences sudden acceleration
the accelerator pedal sticks
the accelerator pedal does not return to its normal position
the accelerator pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unintended acceleration of the vehicle, combined with the failure of the brakes, can lead to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates rapidly and unexpectedly
the RPMs soar
the brakes fail to respond
the vehicle continues to move despite being in park or neutral gear
the driver is unable to stop the vehicle using the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal linkage can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal does not respond
the vehicle does not slow down or stop when the brakes are applied
the brake pedal linkage is broken or damaged.
